		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="align(right)">Congregation Shearith Israel&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44;    <date>9th Shebat 5628</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>2d Feby 1868</date></p>
				<p>At a meeting of the Board of Trustees held this day the following<lb/> resolutions were unanimously adopted&#58;</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> &#8212; that the Trustees of the Congregation <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> learn with sincere regret of the death of the <persName>Reverend<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Isaac Leeser</hi></persName> the much respected <add>Hebrew</add> of the Congn<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> &#8212; distinguished alike for<lb/> his many virtues&#44; his fearless devotion to the House of<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName> during a long period of usefulness&#44; and with an<lb/> ability which marked him as the earnest champion of<lb/> orthodox Judaism.</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> &#8212; that we tender the Congregation <add>Hebrew</add> our warmest<lb/> sympathies for their severe bereavement&#44; and offer the<lb/> assurance of our respect and condolence on the melancholy<lb/> occasion.<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Resolved </hi>&#8212; that the <add>Hebrew</add> of this Congn&#44; the <persName>Revd I. I. Lyons</persName>&#44; be requested<lb/> to make an Escoba in our Holy place of worship on<lb/> then ensuing <add>Hebrew</add> for the Reverend deceased&#44; and also on<lb/> the expiration of the <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
				<p><hi rend="underline">Resolved</hi> &#8212; that&#44; as a further mark to respect for the deceased&#44; and<lb/> for the congregation he so faithfully and creditably served&#44;</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>a committee from this Board with the <add>Hebrew</add> of the<lb/> Congregation be requested to attend the <add>Hebrew</add> at <placeName>Philada</placeName><lb/> and to present to the President of the Congregation <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> a copy of these Resolutions&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline">Extract from the minutes</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Mark<add>&#63;</add> Phillips</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Clerk</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>Resolutions</p>
				<p>Cong Shearith Israel</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>NY</placeName></p>
		</body>
